        h2 Premise

        p SocialForm approached me to do a complete overhaul of Splatt, their existing photo enhancement suite, which was completely web-based at the time.

        p Splatt let users modify their photos with filters and illustrated overlays. The goal was to take instagramâ€™s image editing suite a few steps further, with animated filters, props, and text features, accessible via in-app purchases.

        p This project took place in the days of iOS6, before this idea caught on hugely with snapchat, so while it feels a little derivitave today, much of this was novel at the time.

        hr

        h2 User Flows

        p I started the project by tightly defining the scope of the new application,  which was a fairly standard profile-based social media app with an attached store and image-editing modal.
    
